## 4️⃣ Quick sanity‑check in the REPL

```ocaml
# #require "blocksci";;
# Blocksci.iter_blocks (fun b -> if b.Blocksci.height mod 1_000_000 = 0 then
#                                 Printf.printf "Reached %d\n%!" b.Blocksci.height);;
Reached 0
Reached 1000000
Reached 2000000
…
```

The callback is executed once every million blocks, proving that the OCaml
function is indeed called from inside the C++ iterator while the rest of the
iteration runs at native speed.

